description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered nurse and looking for a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about supporting cardiac patients in the community setting?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an opportunity to develop your skills and knowledge in a dynamic and forward thinking team?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Leeds Community Cardiac Services Team is made up of specialist nurses, physiotherapist, occupational therapist and clinical support workers providing cardiac rehabilitation for patients following acute cardiac events and those with heart failure. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are looking for a passionate, dynamic and flexible individual who is able to adapt to changing demands and workload. This is an ideal opportunity if you wish to develop your skills within this specialist service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main duties of this role involve managing and running the cardiac rehabilitation health, education and exercise programmes across various sites citywide as well as assessing and supporting patients in their own homes. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Experience in cardiology is desirable but not essential as you will be fully supported to develop your skills and knowledge. You will be a good team player, but also be able to work independently in the community. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates Monday to Friday, 08:30 - 16:30 and it is essential that you are able to travel independently across the city and have access to a suitable vehicle for business purposes. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For informal enquiries please contact: &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Nicki Simpson, Community Cardiac Physiotherapist on 07904 169 181&lt;/p&gt;
